\subsection{With Python}

\begin{note}
Python has a built-in module \texttt{glob} for globbing.
The function \texttt{glob.glob} returns a list of all paths that match the glob expression.
\end{note}

\begin{note}
The problems below are identical to problems in the previous section,
except that a python file \texttt{example.py} is created and the glob calculated inside this file.
DO NOT FORGET THAT THE \texttt{example.py} FILE MIGHT MATCH THE GLOB PATTERNS!
\end{note}

